  "description": "Write a SQL query to compute the requested aggregate metric.\n\n### Tables\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE users (\n  user_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  plan TEXT NOT NULL,\n  country TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE sessions (\n  session_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id INTEGER NOT NULL,\n  started_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  duration_minutes INTEGER NOT NULL,\n  device TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE purchases (\n  purchase_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id INTEGER NOT NULL,\n  purchased_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  amount INTEGER NOT NULL\n);\n```\n\n### Task\nReturn users whose session count is above their country average session count per user.\n\n### Return Columns\n- `user_id`\n- `user_name`\n- `country`\n- `session_count`\n- `country_avg_sessions`\n\n### Ordering\nSort by `user_id` ASC.\n\n### Notes\n- Use SQLite syntax.\n- Write your answer in `solution.sql`.\n- Do not hardcode output rows; query from tables.\n- Internal hidden tests run against additional seed data.",
